    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-28T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-28T19:00:00-05:00" n="380"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1837: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-28T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 28, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>79. Department’s 57, March 6 and your 61, March 11. British Government is
                    informed Japanese plan material increase in diplomatic staff at Tehran. Please
                    again approach Iranian Government and urge severance of diplomatic relations
                    with Japan. You may state that American Government attaches great importance to
                    this question and that our attitude toward Iranian requests for economic
                    assistance will undoubtedly be affected by Iranian action in this respect.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
